===== When opener redoubles

Opener has denied a stopper so it's preferable for responder to
declare.
So #2^nd^-round transfers are OFF#.

However, when 2D (transfer to {H}) is doubled and redoubled, we still
need to distinguish between invitational and game-forcing when
responder has [nobr]#{H} + {C}#.
So 2S shows invitational with clubs and #opener uses
reverse-transfers# to ensure that responder declares.

